    B. NODE TKT#

       1. This is the system ticket number assigned automatically.
          There are numerous groups with the capability of
          opening tickets.  The numbers are assigned at the 
          time the ticket is opened (originated) in numerical 
          order, regardless of the group that has opened it.



    C. NODE #

       1. Can be up to 5 digits and must be assigned.  A node
          number must be greater than zero.

       2. In the case of a ticket for an internodal link, use
          the low node number in the node pair.

    D. KERNAL

       1. The kernal host that is assigned to the subject node.

    E. HOST

       1. The host number within the slot if opening with 'H'
          option. If opening ticket as an internodal link, the 
          host field will come up as 'HI NODE # and will be the
          higher node number of the node pair.

    F. SLOT

       1. If using the 'H' option when opening a ticket for a
          host problem, the SLOT field will appear.  Enter the
          identifying software slot number the host resides in.

    G. PORTS

       1. Will only be in the header if ticket is opened as a host
          ticket using the 'H' option. Enter the identifying port
          number.
                
       2. If problem with the slot is a specific port, the port 
          number will be entered here.

