         V. MAINTENANCE CONTRACTS AND BILLABLES

            A. MAINTENANCE CONTRACTS

               Categorized as B1, B2, B3, B4, B5 and A

               Customers are charged according to the above plans.
               See Appendix F for a complete description.
               For instance B2 is maintenance service provided
               Monday through Friday 08:00 to 24:00 local time.
               Outside of this maintenance period the customer is
               billed - see below.

               The ticket header has a field for entering the
               maintenance plan. When using the G command enter
               a #29 to change it.

            B. BILLABLE

               If a customer requests maintenance outside of
               the maintenance contract they are informed
               that the dispatch is billable.

               A Billable Service Call form is filled out 
               by the technician.

               When the field engineer has dispatched to the 
               site, the needed information is received, such
               as time of travel to site, parts used and arrival
               and departure times. This is then entered on the 
               billable form and submitted to the appropriate BT
               Tymnet person.

               Other reasons for Billable Calls:

               Customer has caused the problem.
               No trouble found. 
               Customer moved equipment and is requesting reinstallation.
               Customer has denied access to the site after
               the Field Engineer has dispatched.
               Dispatch occurred during contract covered period but
               customer requested Field Engineer remain on site 
               after covered period.



                                                                             






        VI. ESCALATIONS

            A. Managerial escalations are made to all BT Tymnet and third
               party support groups following specific time frames to
               guarantee the quality of service provided to the customer.

               'Escalate' means that the network technician makes a
               phone call to the superior of the person assigned to
               the ticket (support group). The technician informs the
               superior of the ticket and of the non-resolution or
               non-status of the problem.

               If the superior cannot be reached, the next higher level
               of management is informed.

            B. Time frames for escalation vary according to the severity
               level that has been assigned to the ticket. They are as 
               follows:


                    SEVERITY      STATUS EVERY        ESCALATE AFTER

                      1              2 hours             4 hours
                      2              4   "              12   "    
                      3             12   "              24   "
                      4             24   "              at control group
                                                        manager's discretion
        
               1. Whatever support group  the ticket is assigned to
                  for resolution must provide status according to
                  the time frame for that severity. 
                            
                  Example: The ticket is a severity 2 and is over to 
                           Novadyne to dispatch and perform maintenance.
                           The support group should provide status at 
                           least every 4 hours.
        
               2. The problem should be resolved within the 'ESCALATE'
                  time frames above.  A severity 3 must be resolved
                  within 24 hours or it is escalated.


            C. When an escalation is instituted the technician does
               the following:

               1. Issue the command 'E' in the ticket system.
                  Or '7' after an 'S'. See Section VI

               2. Enter ticket number when prompted.








               3. The program will then want to know what type
                  of escalation is being performed.  

                  The screen prompt is:

               WHICH DISCIPLINE WAS THE ESCALATION PERFORMED UNDER ?
                     1 = HARDWARE
                     2 = SOFTWARE
                     3 = TELCO
                     4 = CUSTOMER
               ENTER SELECTION :


               4. The next prompt will be for the level of escalation:
 
               ENTER THE LEVEL OF SOFTWARE ESCALATION THAT YOU HAVE PERFORMED..
                     1 = NONE
                     2 = DISTRICT
                     3 = REGIONAL
                     4 = DIRECTOR
                     5 = EXEC. DIR.
                     6 = VICE PRES.
               ENTER THE NUMBER :
                   
                  The final prompt is for the name of the person
