                                  APPENDIX E
        
                                   DEFERMENT
        






         The following guidelines/rules govern deferment of a ticket.
        
             1. No customer site access. i.e., site closed from 6:00 pm
                to 6:00 am - ticket would be deferred 12 hours.
        
             2. Customer requested delay of repair - ticket would
                be deferred for the requested period of time.
        
             3. An outage occurs outside of the customer's principle
                period of maintenance and the customer does not want
                a service call made.

                i.e., customer has a maintenance contract effective from
                8:00 am to 6:00 pm Monday through Friday; they ex-
                perience an outage at 6:00 pm Friday night and want
                the hardware dispatch at 8:00 am Monday; the ticket
                would be deferred 62 hours.

             4. Tickets are not deferred while awaiting parts from a 
                Field Service Vendor.


                * Note - It is not necessary to defer a ticket if the
                         resolve time is set up.

        
               
             



                                                                            


            

