                               CLOSEOUT CODES






       
                          CLOSE OUT CODE DESCRIPTIONS


             1. NTF          No trouble found or cleared by a dump and
                             reload.

             2. HARDWARE     BT Tymnet hardware was replaced, repaired, 
                             adjusted.

             3. SOFTWARE     BT Tymnet software was modified - node or slot 
                             code.

             4. UNKNOWN      The problem could not be identified and 
                             cleared before the source of the problem
                             could be isolated.

             5. CUST IND     Customer induced. Customer caused the outage.

             6. POWER        Problem resulted from a power outage either
                             scheduled or unscheduled.

             7. COMMON CARR  Common Carrier - The outage was a result of
                             malfunctioning telephone company leased 
                             line or dialup line.
         
             8. O.E.M.       Other Equipment Manufacturer - eg modems.
                             O.E.M. traditionally stands for Original
                             Equipment Manufacture.

             9. PERIPHERALS  Any Tymnet input/output devices attached
                             locally or remotely to an engine. eg tape drive

            10. DEAD ENDED   Equipment was down because its upstream node
                             connection to the network was down.

            11. PROJECT      Implementation of a project.
         
        








